external_knowledge:
- The 'captain of the ship' refers to the CEO of the company; 
- The 'waters it sails in' refers to the industry the company operates in; 
- The 'treasure collected' refers to the revenue; 
- The 'voyage' refers to a fiscal year.

sql:
SELECT changes 
FROM company_versions 
ORDER BY version_date DESC;

external_knowledge:
Most recent information; 
Latest version: the version with the highest version number; 
Latest financial data: the data with the highest fiscal year; 
Latest SEC filing: the filing with the most recent filing date; 
Latest GICS classification: the classification with the most recent effective date.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT company_id
FROM sec_filings
WHERE filing_date >= datetime('now', '-1 year');
